"Setting the follow mode characters to be better on Dvorak Keyboard layout.
set hintchars=aoeuhtns\',.crlid
set hinttimeout=250

"Also adding mappings appropriate for scrolling quicker with Dvorak.
nnoremap t 5j
nnoremap <Down> 5j
nnoremap T 10j
nnoremap n 5k
nnoremap <Up> 5j
nnoremap N 10k
nnoremap h 5h
nnoremap H H
nnoremap s 5l
nnoremap S L

"Dvorak stuff again; o instead of f for follow.
nnoremap o f
nnoremap O F

"I'm used to QWERTY ctrl-L for selecting the search/address bar, and it's on the homerow now.
noremap <M-N> <M-L>
inoremap <M-N> <M-L>

" we have to open windows somehow
noremap <M-L> <M-N>

"nnoremap <M-T> :tabopen google.co.uk<cr> 
"inoremap <M-T> <esc>:tabopen google.co.uk<cr> 

nnoremap <M-C-T> :tabopen private:about:blank<cr><M-L>
inoremap <M-C-T> <esc>:tabopen private:about:blank<cr><M-L>

inoremap <M-T> <Esc><M-T>

inoremap <c-E> <Esc>
nnoremap <c-E> <Esc>

nnoremap d <M-W>
nnoremap / <M-F>

"Cmd-shift-t to open a private window.
inoremap <M-S-t> <M-S-p>
nnoremap <M-S-t> <M-S-p>

"Idek what caret mode is
noremap c <NOP>

"Ctrl-t is my mapping for logging in.
noremap <C-T> <Esc>

"Standard vim stuff.
nnoremap ; :
nnoremap : ;
